snippet: The killing of the soldier, reportedly by a Palestinian teenager, injected further uncertainty into peace talks, already in deep crisis over Israeli settlement plans in the West Bank.
abstract: Israeli police say a Palestinian teenager fatally stabbed an Israeli soldier on a bus in northern Israel, injecting further uncertainty into already fragile peace talks.

byline.contributor: Jodi Rudoren and Said Ghazali contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: The killing of the soldier, reportedly by a Palestinian teenager, injected further uncertainty into peace talks, already in deep crisis over Israeli settlement plans in the West Bank.

headline.main: Attack on Israeli Worsens Tensions With Palestinians
